{
  "texts": [
    "c Analysis of the number of diverse groups of scaffolds generated per method.",
    "Scaffolds were clustered together if they had a Tanimoto similarity (computed on extended connectivity fingerprints) larger than 60%.",
    "For each plot, the solid line indicates the median obtained across the five analyzed protein targets (PKM2, MAPK1, mTORC1, and TP53) with ten runs each (n = 50), and the shaded area indicates the inter-quartile range.",
    "The statistics per individual target can be found in Supplementary Fig. 3.",
    "Source data are provided as a Source Data file."
  ]
}